reviews.review_text:
This Is what the Grateful Dead is  The first set is pasked full of exicitement. Each song played wide open. Jerry is sooooo on. I don't want to use words like Jerry's on fire,hot, smokeing even though all are true. It's more like he is music and the music is him.Killer rapunctios stranger. Nice tones in peggy-o that grow into a awesome solo. booby is in the mix well also.Tom thumbs is one of the best.Let it grow is one of the highlights. Yes thats righ Let it Grow one of the highlights of an already verry very nice set.
If you are like me and really like the jazz free form something diffrent about this song this time shows. You will love this one.
espicially the Second set a Jazz masterpice that i think one day will be ranked with the John coltrain, Miles Davis, Louis Armstrong free form jazz disscusions. The sultyties and quiet spots that grow into a frenzzy are what make the second set so amazing.Highs and lows Like only the Dead could do....
